{"article_id":"lEBtEprM7aCwybAL","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"WASHINGTON-Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu , in a dramatic and highly public showdown with a U.S. president , told a joint session of Congress Tuesday","depth":8},{"id":1,"text":"that an emerging diplomatic agreement with Iran would not only fail to stop Tehran from acquiring nuclear weapons ,","depth":9},{"id":2,"text":"but virtually ensure","depth":10},{"id":3,"text":"it gets them .","depth":10},{"id":4,"text":"\" This is a bad deal .","depth":11},{"id":5,"text":"It ' s a very bad deal .","depth":11},{"id":6,"text":"We ' re better off without it , \"","depth":10},{"id":7,"text":"Mr. Netanyahu said in a 40-minute address","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"that drew repeated standing ovations in a House chamber","depth":11},{"id":9,"text":"packed mostly with Republican lawmakers .","depth":11},{"id":10,"text":"President Barack Obama , in remarks from the Oval Office a short time later , accused Mr. Netanyahu of sounding an alarm on a deal","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"that isn ' t final","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"while failing to offer \" any viable alternatives \" to the current negotiations","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"involving the U.S. , U.K. , France , Germany , Russia and China .","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"Those talks began two years ago","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"after Mr. Obama personally launched an initiative","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"to engage Iran","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"despite 34 years of frozen ties .","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"Concern for the potential unraveling of Washington ' s long tradition of bipartisan support for Israel was at least one area","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"where Messrs. Obama and Netanyahu agreed .","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"Still , the divisions between the two ,","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"playing out so publicly on opposite ends of Pennsylvania Avenue ,","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"underscore how severely strained relations between Israel and the U.S. have grown .","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"The increasingly partisan overtone was demonstrated","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"when about 50 Democrats boycotted Mr. Netanyahu ' s speech","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"because it was organized by Republican leaders of the new GOP-controlled Congress","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"without consultation with the White House .","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"Mr. Netanyahu ,","depth":6},{"id":28,"text":"who flew back to Israel","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"where he faces an election in two weeks ,","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"left in his wake a growing battle between Congress and the White House over Iran nuclear talks ,","depth":6},{"id":31,"text":"which continue this week in Geneva ahead of an end-of-March deadline .","depth":6},{"id":32,"text":"Mr. Obama said","depth":6},{"id":33,"text":"he didn ' t watch Mr. Netanyahu ' s speech","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"but read the transcript .","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"He urged","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"Congress to reserve judgment on a deal","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"until one is reached .","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"\" The alternative","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"that the prime minister offers","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"is no deal , \"","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"Mr. Obama said ,","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"\" in which case Iran will immediately begin , once again , pursuing its nuclear program ,","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"accelerating its nuclear program ,","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"without us having any insight into what they ' re doing","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"and without restraint . \"","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"Mr. Obama promised to make his case to Congress","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"if there is a final deal","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"and said","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"it would be \" a great mistake \" to derail talks now .","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"\" Let ' s wait","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"until there ' s actually a deal on the table","depth":13},{"id":52,"text":"that Iran has agreed to ,","depth":13},{"id":53,"text":"at which point everybody can evaluate it , \"","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"Mr. Obama said .","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"\" And what I can guarantee","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"is","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"if it is a deal","depth":13},{"id":58,"text":"I signed off on ,","depth":13},{"id":59,"text":"I will be able to prove","depth":12},{"id":60,"text":"that it is the best way for us","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"to prevent Iran from getting a nuclear weapon . \"","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"Mr. Netanyahu is counting on Congress to intervene on the path","depth":7},{"id":63,"text":"the Obama administration is taking in the negotiations .","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"Senate Republican leaders responded later Tuesday","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"by moving forward on legislation","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"that would impose congressional authority","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"to review any final deal .","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"Lawmakers also could pass new sanctions on Iran","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"while talks are ongoing ,","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"which they have signaled","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"they may do after a late March deadline in the talks .","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"Mr. Obama has said","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"he would veto any additional sanctions .","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"Mr. Netanyahu directly challenged Mr. Obama ' s argument","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"that a diplomatic accord","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"allowing Tehran to retain some nuclear capabilities","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"would be more effective than additional sanctions or military action .","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"He said","depth":7},{"id":79,"text":"any agreement","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"that stops short of completely dismantling Iran ' s nuclear program","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"which","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"ehran has said","depth":12},{"id":83,"text":"s for peaceful purposes-w","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"uld be ineffective . F","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"llowing Mr. Netanyahu ' s appearance , I","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"an ' s Foreign Ministry dismissed the address as repetitive and deceitful in its description of Iran ' s intentions . I","depth":7},{"id":87,"text":"NA , the state news agency , quoted ministry spokeswoman Marzieh Afkham a","depth":7},{"id":88,"text":"saying t","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"e mixed reception for Mr. Netanyahu in Washington was a symbol of his isolation , \" even among those w","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"o supported the Zionist regime . \" T","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"e public upbraiding of Mr. Obama ' s negotiations carries tremendous risks for the Israeli leader and his country a","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"he seeks re-election in two weeks , A","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"erican and Israeli officials said . A","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"y apparent fraying of U.S. support for the Jewish state could unnerve Israeli voters . \"","depth":7},{"id":95,"text":"Israel must remain a bipartisan issue among our long-standing American friends , a","depth":8},{"id":96,"text":"d it is unfortunate that the prime minister helped to stir rough political waters in Washington , \" s","depth":8},{"id":97,"text":"id Israeli Labor Party member Erel Margalit , a top opposition figure , on Monday in Washington . I","depth":7},{"id":98,"text":"aac Herzog , Mr. Netanyahu ' s main leftist challenger in Israeli elections this month , reiterated accusations t","depth":5},{"id":99,"text":"at the speech would backfire on Israel a","depth":6},{"id":100,"text":"d cause damage to Israel ' s ties with the U.S . T","depth":6},{"id":101,"text":"e mano-a-mano between Messrs. Netanyahu and Obama showed little space for agreement . M","depth":6},{"id":102,"text":". Netanyahu called on the U.S. to use the nuclear talks as leverage t","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"force Iran to change its behavior , s","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"ch as including provisions r","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"quiring the Iranian regime to stop supporting terrorism and threatening Israel . \"","depth":9},{"id":106,"text":"Iran has proven time and again t","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"at it can not be trusted , \" h","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"said . S","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"ch a move would expand the scope of the international nuclear talks . M","depth":8},{"id":110,"text":". Obama rejected Mr. Netanyahu ' s idea , s","depth":8},{"id":111,"text":"ressing the importance t","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"at the negotiations remain focused solely on Iran ' s nuclear program . O","depth":9},{"id":113,"text":"ama administration officials have long said n","depth":9},{"id":114,"text":"clear talks aren ' t aimed at a broader rapprochement with Iran . \"","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"The specific problem t","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"at is being debated right now i","depth":11},{"id":117,"text":"not whether we trust the Iranian regime or not-we don ' t trust them , \" M","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":". Obama said . M","depth":9},{"id":119,"text":". Netanyahu objected to any deal t","depth":9},{"id":120,"text":"at would leave Iran with significant uranium enrichment capacity , or within 10 years o","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"being able to resume a broader nuclear program . M","depth":10},{"id":122,"text":". Obama said this week t","depth":9},{"id":123,"text":"at a final deal is likely to include a time frame of at least 10 years . M","depth":9},{"id":124,"text":". Netanyahu said l","depth":9},{"id":125,"text":"fting economic sanctions would embolden Tehran to \" sponsor even more terrorism \" a","depth":10},{"id":126,"text":"d the emerging nuclear agreement would set off a nuclear arms race in the Middle East . M","depth":10},{"id":127,"text":". Obama pointedly noted t","depth":9},{"id":128,"text":"at Mr. Netanyahu had opposed an interim nuclear agreement a","depth":12},{"id":129,"text":"opted in 2013 , w","depth":12},{"id":130,"text":"ich h","depth":12},{"id":131,"text":"said h","depth":12},{"id":132,"text":"s kept Iran from progressing toward a nuclear weapon a","depth":11},{"id":133,"text":"d of which Mr. Netanyahu supported an extension . S","depth":11},{"id":134,"text":"me Democrats were disappointed with Mr. Netanyahu ' s overall tone , b","depth":7},{"id":135,"text":"t others agreed with some of his points . S","depth":7},{"id":136,"text":"n. Dianne Feinstein (","depth":10},{"id":137,"text":"D. , Calif. ) , s","depth":10},{"id":138,"text":"id afterward t","depth":9},{"id":139,"text":"at a potential 10-year time frame isn ' t long enough a","depth":9},{"id":140,"text":"d should be extended to 15 or 20 years . B","depth":9},{"id":141,"text":"t House Minority Leader Nancy Pelosi (","depth":11},{"id":142,"text":"D. , Calif. ) s","depth":11},{"id":143,"text":"id s","depth":10},{"id":144,"text":"e found the speech insulting and condescending to past U.S. efforts t","depth":10},{"id":145,"text":"counter Iran a","depth":11},{"id":146,"text":"d support Israel . M","depth":11},{"id":147,"text":". Pelosi said s","depth":9},{"id":148,"text":"e was \" saddened by the condescension toward our knowledge of the threat p","depth":11},{"id":149,"text":"sed by Iran a","depth":11},{"id":150,"text":"d our broader commitment t","depth":11},{"id":151,"text":"preventing nuclear proliferation . \" M","depth":11},{"id":152,"text":"ny congressional Republicans wholeheartedly endorsed Mr. Netanyahu ' s critique of the talks b","depth":7},{"id":153,"text":"ing led by the Obama administration . S","depth":7},{"id":154,"text":"n. Ted Cruz (","depth":10},{"id":155,"text":"R. , Texas ) , s","depth":10},{"id":156,"text":"id t","depth":9},{"id":157,"text":"e address was \" Churchillian , \" c","depth":9},{"id":158,"text":"mparing it to the famed British prime minister . \"","depth":9},{"id":159,"text":"Like a lion in winter , Prime Minister Netanyahu is speaking with a clarity and a gravity about the threat a","depth":9},{"id":160,"text":"nuclear Iran poses to the existence of the nation of Israel , and to the safety and security of America , \" M","depth":9},{"id":161,"text":". Cruz said . -","depth":8},{"id":162,"text":"Michael R. Crittenden and Aresu Eqbali contributed to this article .","depth":1}],"relations":[{"parent":325,"left":324,"right":162,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":324,"left":247,"right":323,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":247,"left":194,"right":246,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":194,"left":189,"right":193,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":189,"left":180,"right":188,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":180,"left":176,"right":179,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":176,"left":166,"right":175,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":166,"left":0,"right":165,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":165,"left":1,"right":164,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":164,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":175,"left":171,"right":174,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":171,"left":168,"right":170,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":168,"left":167,"right":6,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":167,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"restatement","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":170,"left":7,"right":169,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":169,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":174,"left":172,"right":173,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":172,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":173,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":179,"left":14,"right":178,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":178,"left":15,"right":177,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"}